# Phase 2: Data Preprocessing

## Objective

The objective of this phase is to prepare the cleaned dataset for machine learning by transforming it into a suitable format for model training.

---

## Encoding Categorical Data

Categorical features such as Gender were converted into numerical format using one-hot encoding. This step ensures that machine learning algorithms can process categorical information effectively.

---

## Data Transformation

The Final_Grade column was already in numerical form, so no additional mapping was required. A new feature called Result was created to classify students as pass (1) or fail (0) based on their final grade.

---

## Feature Selection

Irrelevant columns such as Student_ID and Student_Name were removed. Feature importance was analyzed using correlation, and only meaningful features were retained for further processing.

---

## Data Standardization

Standardization was applied using StandardScaler to scale the feature values. This ensures that all features have a mean of 0 and a standard deviation of 1, which improves model performance.

---

## Class Imbalance

The dataset was checked for class imbalance using the Result column. The distribution was approximately balanced (around 60–40), so no special techniques such as oversampling or undersampling were required.

---

## Final Output

After preprocessing, the dataset:

* Contains only relevant features
* Has categorical data encoded
* Is scaled and ready for model training

---

## Conclusion of Phase 2

This phase successfully prepared the dataset for machine learning by applying encoding, transformation, feature selection, and scaling techniques. The processed data is now suitable for building and evaluating predictive models.
